<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-11-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-11-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="208" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d208">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 16387/1.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Morgan</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-11-07"><hi rend="italic">November 7,
                                1908</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Root instructs Mr. Morgan to convey to the family of the late Don
                            Tomas Estrada Palma an expression of deep sorrow and sympathy in their
                            bereavement. Mr. Root states that he mourns the death of Don Tomas
                            Estrada Palma as the loss of a personal friend as well as a noble pure
                            minded lover of his country.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>